---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy -- Prompt-Armor" description="Privacy policy for Prompt-Armor as required by GDPR.">
  <Header />

  <main class="flex-1 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-armor-white mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-xs text-armor-muted mb-8">Last updated: March 14, 2026</p>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-sm text-armor-text leading-relaxed">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">1. Controller</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          The controller responsible for data processing on this website is:
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Belkis Aslani<br/>
          Vogelsangstr. 32<br/>
          71691 Freiberg am Neckar<br/>
          Germany<br/>
          Email:
          <a href="mailto:belkis.aslani@gmail.com" class="text-armor-accent hover:text-armor-accent-hover transition-colors">
            belkis.aslani@gmail.com
          </a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">2. Overview of data processing</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          Prompt-Armor is designed with privacy in mind. <strong class="text-armor-white">All prompt encoding
          and decoding happens entirely in your browser.</strong> No prompt data is ever sent to a server.
          We do not collect, store, or process any prompts you enter.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">3. Hosting</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          This website is hosted on <strong class="text-armor-white">GitHub Pages</strong>, a service provided by
          GitHub, Inc. (88 Colin P. Kelly Jr. St., San Francisco, CA 94107, USA). When you visit this website,
          GitHub may collect technical data such as your IP address in server log files. This is necessary for
          the delivery of the website and constitutes a legitimate interest pursuant to Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR.
        </p>
        <p class="text-armor-muted mt-3">
          For more information, see GitHub's privacy statement:
          <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement"
             target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
             class="text-armor-accent hover:text-armor-accent-hover transition-colors">
            GitHub Privacy Statement
          </a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">4. Google Fonts</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          This website uses the font "JetBrains Mono" loaded from Google Fonts, a service by Google LLC
          (1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, USA). When you load a page, your browser
          establishes a connection to Google's servers to retrieve the font files. Google may receive your
          IP address in this process.
        </p>
        <p class="text-armor-muted mt-3">
          The use of Google Fonts is based on our legitimate interest in a uniform and appealing presentation
          of our website (Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR).
        </p>
        <p class="text-armor-muted mt-3">
          For more information, see:
          <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
             class="text-armor-accent hover:text-armor-accent-hover transition-colors">
            Google Privacy Policy
          </a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">5. Local storage</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          This website uses your browser's <strong class="text-armor-white">localStorage</strong> to store the
          current app version number. This is used solely to detect when a new version has been deployed and
          to show you an update notification. No personal data is stored. You can clear this data at any time
          through your browser settings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">6. Service Worker</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          This website uses a Service Worker to enable offline functionality and faster page loads. The Service
          Worker caches website assets (HTML, CSS, JavaScript, images) in your browser. No personal data is
          cached or transmitted. You can unregister the Service Worker through your browser's developer tools
          at any time.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">7. No cookies</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          This website does <strong class="text-armor-white">not use cookies</strong>. We do not use any
          tracking, analytics, or advertising cookies.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">8. No analytics</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          We do <strong class="text-armor-white">not use any analytics services</strong> (no Google Analytics,
          no Matomo, no tracking pixels, no similar tools). We have no interest in tracking your behavior.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">9. Your rights under GDPR</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          Under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), you have the following rights:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-armor-muted mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Right of access (Art. 15 GDPR)</li>
          <li>Right to rectification (Art. 16 GDPR)</li>
          <li>Right to erasure (Art. 17 GDPR)</li>
          <li>Right to restriction of processing (Art. 18 GDPR)</li>
          <li>Right to data portability (Art. 20 GDPR)</li>
          <li>Right to object (Art. 21 GDPR)</li>
          <li>Right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority (Art. 77 GDPR)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-armor-muted mt-3">
          The competent supervisory authority is the
          <strong class="text-armor-white">Landesbeauftragte fuer den Datenschutz und die Informationsfreiheit
          Baden-Wuerttemberg</strong>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">10. Contact regarding privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          If you have any questions about data protection or wish to exercise your rights, please contact:
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Belkis Aslani<br/>
          Email:
          <a href="mailto:belkis.aslani@gmail.com" class="text-armor-accent hover:text-armor-accent-hover transition-colors">
            belkis.aslani@gmail.com
          </a>
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
